The DEFAULT theme's palette (when no --theme or .drift/theme.xml is active): diff + lines = bright green (92); diff - lines = bright red (91); hunk @@ headers = bright cyan + bold (96;1); [DRIFTED], [deleted], error messages = bright red (91); [TODO], [unlinked], drift status lines = bright yellow (93); [synced], Status: in sync, No changes detected = bright green (92); section headers (=== Spec/Marker ===) = bold (1); marker IDs = bright blue + bold (94;1); spec IDs = bright magenta + bold (95;1); filepaths/locations = dim (2); hashes = dim (2); commands/CTAs = bright green (92); hints = bright cyan (96). This spec describes ONE theme; all elements are configurable via the <ref spec="output.theme_system">theme system</ref>.